Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createExclusiveGroups(25.10)                      createExclusiveGroups(25.10)

Name
       createExclusiveGroups - Creates exclusive regions

Syntax
        createExclusiveGroups

       [-help]

       [<group_name>]

       [-gap <float>]

       [-min_gap <float>]

       [-exclusiveGroups <string> | -mutuallyExclusiveGroups <string>]

       Creates exclusive regions. Exclusive regions specified for a particular
       group  cannot be placed/overlapped with it but they can overlap on each
       other/ any other region in the core area.

Sample Script
       Following is a sample script to create exclusive groups:

       createInstGroup $group_name

       addInstToInstGroup $group_name {insts}

       createInstGroup $group_name1

       addInstToInstGroup $group_name1 {insts}

       createExclusiveGroups $group_name -exclusiveGroups {$groups_name1}

Parameters
       -exclusiveGroups <string>
              Specifies the groups/regions that  cannot  be  placed/overlapped
              with the specified group name.

              For Example:

              If  regions  B,C,D  are  defined  as exclusive regions to A. In-
              stances from B,C,D can never be placed on A. Other regions which
              are not defined exclusive to region A can  be  placed  or  over-
              lapped with region A.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -gap <float>
              Specifies  the  value of the gap, in microns, that is maintained
              among exclusive groups.

              Default: 5 (microns)

              Data_type: float, optional

       <group_name>
              Specifies the name of the created group.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each createExclusiveGroups parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man createExclusiveGroups

       -min_gap <float>
              Specifies the value of the minimum  gap,  in  microns,  that  is
              maintained among exclusive groups.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -mutuallyExclusiveGroups <string>
              Specifies  the groups which need to be excluded with each other.
              You can independently use this option to specify and create mul-
              tiple mutually exclusive groups.

              Note: If a group  has  already  been  defined  as  an  exclusive
              groups, then a second setting for this group using the createEx-
              clusiveGroups  command  will give display an error that suggests
              you to reset the exclusive groups attributes to  default  value.
              If  you want to create mutually exclusive groups, then reset the
              exclusive groups attributes using the deleteExclusiveGroups com-
              mand and then create the mutually  exclusive  groups  using  the
              createExclusiveGroups -mutuallyExclusiveGroups command.

              Data_type: string, optional

Examples
              * The following commands define gr_300 as an exclusive region to
                gr_200:

                createInstGroup gr_200

                addInstToInstGroup     gr_200    DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXE-
                CUTE_INST/acc_reg*

                createInstGroup gr_300

                addInstToInstGroup    gr_300     DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST/EXE-
                CUTE_INST/top_reg_*

                createExclusiveGroups gr_200 -exclusiveGroups gr_300

              * The  following  commands defines instance groups A, B, C to be
                mutually exclusive groups with a space of 10  microns  between
                each other.

                createExclusiveGroups -mutuallyExclusiveGroups {A B C} -gap 10

Related Information
